<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">LET IT SNOW <span class="divider"> | </span></span> A major snowstorm is heading toward New York City, and the snowpocalypse-induced hysteria is at its peak. On Sunday, Mayor Bill de Blasio <b><a href="//www.nytimes.com/2015/01/26/nyregion/de-blasio-urges-new-yorkers-to-prepare-for-powerful-snowstorm.html">urged people to stay indoors</a></b> and told New Yorkers to âprepare for something worse than we have seen before.â</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">The snowfall will probably be heaviest Monday night into Tuesday morning, Mr. de Blasio said, adding that up to three feet of snow could fall by the time the storm is over. Schools will be open on Monday but will probably close on Tuesday, Mr. de Blasio said.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YUY9Y9RFiHY">Hot chocolate</a></b>, anyone?</p>
